{"sectionId":750,"sectionIdLiteral":"750","humanId":"lesson-328","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"I choose the second place to gain the first.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 328"},"annotation":"W-328","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-328\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"750#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>What seems to be the second place is first, for all things we perceive are upside down until we listen to the Voice for God.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>It seems that we will gain autonomy but by our striving to be separate, and that our independence from the rest of God‚Äôs creation is the way in which salvation is obtained.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Yet all we find is sickness, suffering and loss and death.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>This is not what our Father wills for us, nor is there any second to His Will.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>To join with His is but to find our own.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>And since our will is His, it is to Him that we must go to recognize our will.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"750#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>There is no will but Yours.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>And I am glad that nothing I imagine contradicts what You would have me be.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>It is Your Will that I be wholly safe, eternally at peace.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"750#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And happily I share that Will which You, my Father, gave as part of me.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"What seems to be the second place is first, for all things we perceive are upside down until we listen to the Voice for God. It seems that we will gain autonomy but by our striving to be separate,","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 328: I choose the second place to gain‚Ä¶ | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†328 ‚ÄúI choose the second place to gain the first‚Äù: What seems to be the second place is first, for all things we perceive‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"11. What Is Creation?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":742,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-creation"]}},{"label":"Lesson 328","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":750,"slugs":["lesson-328","i-choose-the-second-place-to-gain-the-first"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"11. What Is Creation?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":742,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-creation"]}},{"label":"Lesson 328","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":750,"slugs":["lesson-328","i-choose-the-second-place-to-gain-the-first"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"11. What Is Creation?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":742,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-creation"]}},{"label":"Lesson 328","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sect